title: Episode dated 10 April 2006
description: Lead story focuses on the planned protests against U.S. immigration policy across 39 states. Other reports look at whether the U.S. is planning a nuclear strike on Iran, a young man calling 911 for help which never came, a gossip columnist involved in possible extortion, an interview with the father of Natalee Holloway, a look at what it is like to be a thirteen year old girl around the world, life with obsessive compulsive disorder, an investigation into the problem with American High Schools, a Canadian man who put his life in danger to save his wedding ring, a breakthrough in stem cell research for lupus, and an interview with Naveen Andrews.

title: Episode dated 10 August 2006
description: Good Morning America covers breaking news about a major terrorist plot uncovered by Britain police. Terrorists were planning to bomb at least nine passenger planes en-route from London to New York. Other reports focus on the Homeland Security and White House responses, an investigation into whether Al Qaeda in involved, and the disruption in travel plans.

title: Episode dated 23 August 2006
description: Chris Cuomo interviews Quientana Ray, the first wife of John Mark Karr, the alleged confessor to the Jonbennet Ramsey murder. She describes a dark individual who was obsessed with death and young girls, who taunted her family with sick letters after he convinced her to run away with him and marry at her age of 13 years, while he was several years her senior. Ms. Ray's father and mother are also interviewed in the segment concerning John Mark Karr.
